Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.25,0:00:04.87,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two people's deductions and suspense\Nfill the gulf between love and hate!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.87,0:00:06.29,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An uninhabited island and the bottom of the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.29,0:00:08.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Conan and Heiji's deductions explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.62,0:00:10.13,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.13,0:00:12.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.02,0:00:14.09,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.54,0:01:46.44,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A TV show pitting the best detectives from the east and west
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.44,0:01:49.08,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}brought us, along with Heiji Hattori, here to Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.86,0:01:54.36,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We went with the film crew to an uninhabited island,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.36,0:01:57.23,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}where an unidentified body and a mysterious message were found.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.28,0:02:02.18,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then Yoshie Taira{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, a female member of the film crew,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.18,0:02:05.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}was found, with a mysterious message next to her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.73,0:02:10.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then the boat we came on, and the captain, vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.46,0:02:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? An anchor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.19,0:02:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found an anchor at the bottom of the sea where Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was diving?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.72,0:02:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.88,0:02:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rusty anchor, with a broken chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.16,0:02:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be from the ship of that guy who died last year!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.40,0:02:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! He dropped anchor here and was waitin' for the typhoon to pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.29,0:02:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the chain on the anchor broke an' his ship got washed away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.55,0:02:47.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That anchor had shells and seaweed all over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.32,0:02:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gotta have been there at least four or five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.37,0:02:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four or five years...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:03:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, that was around the time that strange stuff happened at the mayor's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.57,0:03:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.12,0:03:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.92,0:03:10.62,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Noburo Ikema (24)\NCrew
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.17,0:03:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, the mayor's only daughter, Miss Miyako, was kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.58,0:03:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A year later, burglars broke into the house
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.04,0:03:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and stole a golden folding screen that had been the family treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor and his butler got calls from the criminals both times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.96,0:03:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They think the kidnappers and the burglars were the same people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.45,0:03:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.39,0:03:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor wouldn't meet their ransom demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.06,0:03:40.23,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yoshitsugu Kume (25)\NCrew
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.85,0:03:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminals were never caught, and the young lady and the golden screen are still missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.46,0:03:47.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor's had a hard time of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:49.24,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Masao Taketomi (42)\NTV Director
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.74,0:03:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His daughter was kidnapped around the same time he lost his wife to an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.73,0:03:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the burglars killed his housekeeper, and his butler got scared and quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People called him heartless for refusing to pay the ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.13,0:04:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then a man starved to death on this island, which he owns,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.48,0:04:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that strange message was found next to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.85,0:04:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.88,0:04:20.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really feels like the Emissary of Gusō is after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.00,0:04:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The message said, "The princess sleeps in the {\i1}kō{\i0} and not in the {\i1}otsu{\i0}", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.49,0:04:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the princess is the kidnapped daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think she's been killed and is buried somewhere on this island?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.38,0:04:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.59,0:04:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she came back from the dead as the Emissary and strangled Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're scared of the emissary, take that knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.84,0:04:54.82,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mikihiko Daito (47)\NCrew
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.46,0:05:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The legends say a woman should put a {\i1}sheeg{\i0}, a knife, between her lips
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.31,0:05:03.84,Signs,,0,0,0,,mabui = soul\Nsheeg = knife
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to keep her soul from being pulled out through her mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.84,0:05:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if that doesn't work,\Nyou can use it to stab someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.10,0:05:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.26,0:05:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look at this teacup!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.26,0:05:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been used as an ashtray.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:25.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Different brands of cigarettes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.61,0:05:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the water they were doused in hasn't evaporated yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.08,0:05:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're sayin' somebody was in this cottage before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.08,0:05:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, and there wasn't just one or two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.67,0:05:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever killed that girl, Emissaries of Gusō or common criminals,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.88,0:05:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they're hiding out on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.29,0:05:52.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on! Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.43,0:05:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think the person who killed Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was part of a gang or something hanging out on the island?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.70,0:06:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying it's a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.50,0:06:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there are Emissaries all around us, after our {\i1}mabui{\i0}—our souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.52,0:06:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could they be in the cottage right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! We searched the place when we got here and it was empty, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.32,0:06:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But a lot of the windows are broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.76,0:06:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be a piece of cake to sneak in while we're yappin' away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.39,0:06:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's split up and search again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.38,0:06:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure. Ain't no point sittin' here shiverin' in fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.19,0:06:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kume{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Ikema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Daito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nyou take the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.22,0:06:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.01,0:06:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll search the first floor with Taketomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.40,0:06:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right. There's two girls, but you're the only guy, so you'd be at a disadvantage if you got attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.39,0:06:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are ya mental?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.11,0:06:59.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're the one they'd be protecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.18,0:07:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.12,0:07:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're a karate champ?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.78,0:07:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.54,0:07:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I won a city tournament...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.45,0:07:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a second {\i1}dan{\i0} in Aikido!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.54,0:07:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow... That's reassuring...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.96,0:07:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:16.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer appears, leave it all to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.02,0:07:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good thing I asked that guy to stick with us, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.03,0:07:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he'd be toast on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.19,0:07:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-All right, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}... t-this is the last room...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't keep us hangin', hurry an' open it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.96,0:07:40.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe this wasn't such a good idea after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey... Anybody here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.68,0:07:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.60,0:07:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks deserted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.96,0:07:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a lot bigger than the other rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because it's the mayor's wife's bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.42,0:08:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, here's a photo of the mayor and his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really rusty...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.78,0:08:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're ya doin', Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.95,0:08:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two photos in this frame...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.33,0:08:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? A picture of the mayor with a young babe!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.08,0:08:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I betcha this guy was havin' an affair!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.08,0:08:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's his only daughter, Miss Miyako!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.55,0:08:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a lot like her mother, beautiful, with pale, silky skin, and very kind and gentle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.52,0:08:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The whole island talked about who she'd end up marrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.76,0:08:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But while she was at junior college, she was kidnapped and disappeared forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.03,0:08:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you were from a TV station in Kyushu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come you know all the local gossip?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.53,0:09:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Yoshiko Matsumoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the mayor's housekeeper, was my cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.96,0:09:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me all about the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.76,0:09:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was your cousin the housekeeper who died?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:13.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the burglary?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Four years ago, one of the burglars killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.90,0:09:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of cousins, Ikema{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother was the mayor's wife's sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.81,0:09:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he and the young lady were cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's that castle in the background? I don't recognize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not a castle! It's the mayor's house!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.62,0:09:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a big mansion, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.67,0:09:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what Yoshiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.61,0:09:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss Miyako was a little girl when the house was built, and she loved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.29,0:09:49.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She felt like she'd turned into a real princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.99,0:09:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The princess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.43,0:09:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of the castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.47,0:09:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the "princess" in that strange message really does mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.54,0:09:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The young lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.33,0:10:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are strange words on this pillar too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.39,0:10:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that young lady wrote these.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.95,0:10:10.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, three of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.06,0:10:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. Looks like they were written in crayon or somethin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.59,0:10:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the very top is "Brother Chiyo"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About 20 cm below that is "{\i1}kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An' at the very bottom it says, "me".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.54,0:10:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judgin' from the number of marks around "me",
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.38,0:10:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the young lady kept comparin' heights with the other two when she came here as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.20,0:10:39.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez. Don't scare me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.77,0:10:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's funny, though. "{\i1}Kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}" is a weird thing to call your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.52,0:10:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially a rich, well-bred little girl like Miyako.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think "{\i1}kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}" is her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:52.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this! It's starting to fade,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.56,0:10:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but there's more writing on the door using the same crayon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mama's room"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.13,0:10:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So who were they?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.04,0:11:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This "{\i1}Kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}" and "Brother Chiyo"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.30,0:11:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.98,0:11:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they were friends from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.24,0:11:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so! Look how tall they were!\NDo these look like preschool friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.09,0:11:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.24,0:11:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, these doors have "{\i1}Kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}" and "Brother Chiyo" written on 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.33,0:11:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That room over there is "Brother Chiyo's Room"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.85,0:11:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this here is "{\i1}Kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s Room".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.25,0:11:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ain't all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.63,0:11:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a funny doodle next to the writin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.65,0:11:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one next to "{\i1}Kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}" looks like a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An' the one next to "Brother Chiyo" looks like an eel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking at old kids' drawings in the dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.53,0:11:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is kinda creepy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.94,0:11:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.29,0:11:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if these folks had their own rooms in the summer cottage,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.09,0:11:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they musta come out here with the young lady pretty regular.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.78,0:12:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After we get rescued, I wanna ask the mayor who those two were.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.93,0:12:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they've got somethin' to do with this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.14,0:12:11.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.17,0:12:12.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was Kume{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.26,0:12:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somethin' happened on the second floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.99,0:12:17.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.64,0:12:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.82,0:12:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.34,0:12:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didja find the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.78,0:12:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.16,0:12:37.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy suddenly screamed like a banshee and fell back in a panic
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.78,0:12:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after seeing this painting that was behind the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.56,0:12:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't that the young lady, the girl in the photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.87,0:12:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.04,0:12:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She looks just like that photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.48,0:12:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor's wife must've painted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.92,0:12:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told me she was quite the artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.04,0:13:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.08,0:13:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah, my cousin. She was the mayor's housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.65,0:13:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means there are four people here\Nwith some kind of connection to the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.10,0:13:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.58,0:13:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My mother was the younger sister of the mayor's wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.65,0:13:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The director and the mayor's housekeeper were cousins too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.90,0:13:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kume and the young lady were classmates all through elementary, middle and high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.76,0:13:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Daito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here was a childhood friend of the mayor's wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.83,0:13:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A childhood friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.42,0:13:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.65,0:13:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I visited her grave with my mom last year, and he was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.65,0:13:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When my mom asked him about it, that's what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.40,0:13:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my mom said she didn't remember him, so maybe it was all a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.39,0:13:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no surprise. Your mom was just a little kid then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.44,0:13:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, since your mother and the mayor's wife were sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.87,0:13:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,have you been to this island before?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope. My mom and I hardly ever visited the mayor's house either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.12,0:14:08.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We always felt out of place in those fancy digs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.96,0:14:12.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only saw the young lady a few times\Nwhen she was very young.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:16.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why was Kume{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} scared of that paintin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.53,0:14:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me. Maybe he thought it was her ghost?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.89,0:14:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everybody keeps talking like she's already dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.06,0:14:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Anyway, it doesn't look like there's\Nany suspicious people hiding here,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.42,0:14:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so let's huddle up together in one room\Nand wait for the rescue ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.64,0:14:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. Don't you think it's taking a little too long?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.61,0:14:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.71,0:14:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know that dumb lug.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.77,0:15:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably off gettin' blitzed an' hittin' on girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.01,0:15:03.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ol' dope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.41,0:15:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Could it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.95,0:15:18.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it! It's the rescue ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.78,0:15:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.97,0:15:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.51,0:15:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're over here! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.16,0:15:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's somethin' up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.21,0:15:32.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boat's just sitting there with the lights out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:41.59,Signs,,0,0,0,,I am the Emissary of Gusō
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.07,0:15:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is one mean way to kill a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.23,0:15:55.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer bashed the captain's head in with a lead pipe or somethin', over an' over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.73,0:15:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after he was obviously dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.10,0:16:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he wrapped a rope around the stiff's neck an' hung him off the side of the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.34,0:16:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I am the Emissary of Gusō"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.33,0:16:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Talk about a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.25,0:16:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.97,0:16:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's somebody other than us on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.40,0:16:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's some kind of gang hiding out here that gets off on murdering people!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.14,0:16:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right. When that boat crashed into the dock, we were all inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.51,0:16:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever was piloting this boat is still around here, I'm sure of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.87,0:16:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. A crazy serial killer who calls himself "The Emissary of Gusō".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.73,0:16:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. That might not be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.48,0:16:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.51,0:16:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just looked around the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.64,0:16:51.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's this funny thing that looks like a little TV next to the steering wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.73,0:16:57.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it just told the boat to go around in a big circle from the dock!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.70,0:17:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see... The autopilot! The killer wouldn't have to be on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.70,0:17:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, kid, but with the tidal currents around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.55,0:17:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you couldn't set the autopilot to make an accurate docking. It'd get knocked off-course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.19,0:17:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah, it wouldn't have to be accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.25,0:17:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To deal with tidal currents, an autopilot can be set
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.10,0:17:22.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with a margin of error of about 50-100 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.42,0:17:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the boat was set to hug the shore on this side,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.29,0:17:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it coulda made it 'round the reef an' had a good chance of smashin' into the dock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.30,0:17:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Scrape marks on the side of the hull!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.08,0:17:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boat was movin' along the edge of the coral reef!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.80,0:17:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the murderer coulda used the autopilot
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.28,0:17:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to send this boat out from the dock hours ago\Nwith the body already hangin' from it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.85,0:17:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any one of us coulda done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.30,0:18:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you saying one of us could be the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.11,0:18:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.39,0:18:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y'all followed us outta the boat after we rushed out to look for Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.90,0:18:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The very last person who left the boat coulda done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.71,0:18:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me neither!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the last guy off the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.69,0:18:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.42,0:18:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But anyone could've snuck back on board after I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.76,0:18:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And aren't you forgetting something, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.53,0:18:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think back to when we found that Taira girl's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.68,0:18:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! You said it yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.30,0:18:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those words in the sand next to Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.34,0:18:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of us had time to write them, because we were on the other side of the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.23,0:19:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were written right at the edge of the receding tide,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the murderer could only have written them minutes before we found the body!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.71,0:19:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the same words were written\Nnext to Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.31,0:19:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so it's gotta be the same killer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.73,0:19:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer couldn't be one of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.47,0:19:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if the killer is part of a group?\NOne of us could be an accomplice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.47,0:19:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's just another of his tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.09,0:19:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he wants us to get suspicious of each other and fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.36,0:19:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, at least we've got the boat back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. We can figger out the details\Nonce we get off this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.57,0:19:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope. I checked the boat when I brought the body down, an' the fuel tank's nearly empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.69,0:19:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ain't all. The radio transmitter was trashed an' our bags are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.24,0:19:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.18,0:20:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer wants to keep us\Non the island. He's up to somethin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.56,0:20:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Up to something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.96,0:20:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like another murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If you don't wanna get killed, let's get back in that cottage an' wait for rescue!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.56,0:20:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez. How long are we gonna have to wait for a rescue ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.08,0:20:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.54,0:20:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Heiji, we'll see you back there later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.25,0:20:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.97,0:20:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.26,0:20:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.31,0:20:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ya know, Kudo, this case just don't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.35,0:20:38.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.06,0:20:45.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer carefully folded Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hands an' closed her eyes after killin' her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.35,0:20:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the next victim, the captain,\Ngot beaten to a pulp.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.90,0:20:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's more than one murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.84,0:20:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The methods are too different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.87,0:21:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What also bothers me is the weird final acts of Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.86,0:21:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Taira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} insisted on going diving at night in dangerous waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.54,0:21:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the captain was sailing around in his boat
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when he was supposed to be\Ngetting ready to take us home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.68,0:21:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was sonar equipment on the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.66,0:21:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he was off searchin' for somethin' in the ocean around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.57,0:21:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever was on the other end of that anchor I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.83,0:21:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.78,0:21:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Kudo, didja notice the bottoms of the chairs in the room we were just in?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.18,0:21:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. A child had written on them with crayons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chair I was sitting on said "me",
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.07,0:21:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the chair Ran was sitting on said "mama".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.20,0:21:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for some strange reason, the bottom of the chair I was sittin' on said...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.36,0:21:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kaneshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.94,0:21:50.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The young lady wrote those, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.88,0:21:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Kaneshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was her dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.12,0:21:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why didn't she write "daddy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.33,0:21:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And those were the only three chairs with names on 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.10,0:22:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's strange we didn't find chairs for\N"{\i1}Kaa{\i0\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}" and "Brother Chiyo",
